00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:47.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so why don’t we go home first
so you can leave your bags?

283
00:18:47.626 --> 00:18:49.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll carry one.

284
00:18:49.086 --> 00:18:50.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you so much.

285
00:18:50.629 --> 00:18:53.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is it really okay to stay
at your place again?

286
00:18:53.882 --> 00:18:56.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mm-hmm. You can stay
for as many nights as you wish.

287
00:18:57.052 --> 00:18:58.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s summer vacation,
so you have free time, don’t you?

288
00:18:58.971 --> 00:18:59.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

289
00:18:59.888 --> 00:19:04.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To be honest, I would love to spend all
of my summer vacation here,

290
00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:07.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I couldn’t possibly impose
on you for a full month.

291
00:19:07.187 --> 00:19:08.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s totally okay with me!

292
00:19:08.772 --> 00:19:10.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then spend
your whole summer vacation here!

293
00:19:10.399 --> 00:19:11.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or rather, I want you to stay!

294
00:19:11.608 --> 00:19:14.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you sure? I’m thrilled!

295
00:19:14.194 --> 00:19:15.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m just as glad about it.

296
00:19:15.946 --> 00:19:18.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nana’s staying with Ren…
-<i>A train will be arriving on track one.</i>

297
00:19:18.323 --> 00:19:19.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and shows no sign of returning.

298
00:19:19.449 --> 00:19:21.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I was feeling all lonely living alone.
-<i>Please stay inside the yellow line.</i>

299
00:19:21.743 --> 00:19:22.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
TRAIN IS COMING

300
00:19:25.414 --> 00:19:28.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, I still can’t get
over the excitement

301
00:19:28.375 --> 00:19:31.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
after learning that Nana and Ren
are all lovey-dovey.

302
00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:36.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I carelessly blurted it out.
I assumed you would already know.

303
00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:40.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
But I did secretly find out
when they were back in my hometown

304
00:19:40.804 --> 00:19:42.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
that the two were living together.

305
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:46.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve been wondering what had happened
between them after that,

306
00:19:46.226 --> 00:19:47.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so this news is such a relief to me.

307
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:49.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please don’t tell anyone, okay?

308
00:19:50.063 --> 00:19:53.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Rest assured.
Please have faith in me, Ms. Hachiko.

309
00:19:59.239 --> 00:20:00.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The concert starts at seven, right?

310
00:20:01.074 --> 00:20:04.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can’t wait to see the band members.

311
00:20:04.369 --> 00:20:06.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wonder if they’re still rehearsing.

312
00:20:06.538 --> 00:20:09.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, I haven’t seen them for a week.

313
00:20:09.333 --> 00:20:12.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I thought you visited the studio
every day to see them practice.

314
00:20:13.045 --> 00:20:14.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, yeah, but…

315
00:20:14.838 --> 00:20:16.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn’t wanna bother them
so close to their live performance.

316
00:20:16.924 --> 00:20:19.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see. You’re right.

317
00:20:19.134 --> 00:20:21.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let’s hope that BLAST’s
professional debut becomes a reality.

318
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:23.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

319
00:20:25.933 --> 00:20:30.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If I were to see Nobu today,</i>
<i>what expression should I make?</i>

320
00:20:35.692 --> 00:20:40.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nobu may never smile for me again.</i>

321
00:20:41.782 --> 00:20:45.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That thought almost made me cry.</i>

322
00:20:51.041 --> 00:20:55.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That other night, when Nana sang</i>
<i>that song that Nobu wrote,</i>

323
00:20:55.295 --> 00:20:58.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>she was wishing for something</i>
<i>as she sang it with such passion…</i>

324
00:20:59.132 --> 00:21:02.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>so her voice would reach me.</i>

325
00:21:04.429 --> 00:21:07.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Right now, I realize what she was wishing.</i>

